//
// T122 (a/b) — non-default config: `trailing_commas = "add"`
// appends a comma after the LAST arg in a multi-line
// `proc_name` argument list (per
// `formatting-rules.contract.md` §3 trailing-comma policy +
// §9 rule↔key matrix row R3 ↔ `trailing_commas`; §3 amended
// Session 2026-05-12 — see `plan.md` Plan Revisions).
//
// Default config is `trailing_commas = "preserve"` (the
// pre-format trailing-comma state is kept); this fixture flips
// to `"add"` and verifies the output adds a trailing comma after
// the last arg in the multi-line form. The multi-line form is
// triggered by `max_line_length` overflow on the default 100-col
// budget.
//
// T054 (this commit) implements R3 — fixture flipped
// XFAIL→PASS.

// RUN: rm -rf %t.tc && mkdir -p %t.tc
// RUN: printf 'trailing_commas = "add"\n' > %t.tc/.nsl-fmt.toml
// RUN: printf 'module m { reg argument_one[8]; reg argument_two[8]; reg argument_three[8]; reg argument_four[8]; reg argument_five[8]; reg argument_six[8]; reg argument_seven[8]; proc_name long_arg_proc(argument_one, argument_two, argument_three, argument_four, argument_five, argument_six, argument_seven); }\n' > %t.tc/m.nsl
// RUN: cd %t.tc && nsl-fmt m.nsl | FileCheck %s

// CHECK:         argument_seven,
// CHECK-NEXT:     );
